    <item>
      <title>Technical Design Process</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/toolbox/crafts/technical_design_process/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/toolbox/crafts/technical_design_process/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When the tasks actually needs some careful thought before getting started. Or is too big to jump into codding first. We need to think about technical design.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Design work is broken into two main activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep solitary individual work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative group discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The below diagram is called the &lt;strong&gt;design process spiral&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;The design process spiral&#34; loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/toolbox/Attachments/Pasted%20image%2020260603080939.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Image source: &lt;sup id=&#34;fnref:1&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#fn:1&#34; class=&#34;footnote-ref&#34; role=&#34;doc-noteref&#34;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IMPORTANT&lt;/strong&gt;:  Design is an evolving process with the design document. Making proof of concept also falls under the design process and part of the design spiral.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
